This is the Perl distribution DB-Pluggable-StackTraceAsHTML.

## Installation

DB-Pluggable-StackTraceAsHTML installation is straightforward. If your CPAN
shell is set up, you should just be able to do

    % cpan DB::Pluggable::StackTraceAsHTML

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

## Documentation

DB-Pluggable-StackTraceAsHTML documentation is available as in POD. So you can
do:

    % perldoc DB::Pluggable::StackTraceAsHTML

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

